President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Elisebeth Collins Cook for the position of Member of the Privacy and Civil Liberties Oversight Board. Cook is currently a partner at the law firm Freeborn & Peters LLP, specializing in civil litigation, Constitutional Rights, and administrative law. She previously served as Assistant Attorney General for Legal Policy at the United States Department of Justice, where she focused on national security, civil rights, and regulatory policy. Cook also worked as Senior Counsel and Deputy Assistant Attorney General in the same office. In addition, she served as Republican Chief Counsel for Supreme Court Nominations for the United States Senate Committee on the Judiciary in 2009. Cook holds a B.A. with honors from the University of Chicago and a J.D., cum laude, from Harvard Law School.